{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the handoff between diff-parsing and review-input construction modules (MOCK-MISS yes). Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess required if using captured diff payloads; (b) no AI/ML output dependence; (c) no multi-agentic chain; (d) no LLM-governed stage handoff. Rejection-gate: System is disqualified by behavior text focusing on scoping logic, not real API transport or OS effects.","test_description":"Wire real diff parser + input builder with fixture PR diffs containing unchanged and changed regions; assert only changed hunks are included in the generated review payload and unchanged file bodies are excluded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on real PR diff-position semantics enforced by the hosting API/UI, which mocks often simplify (REAL-INFRA yes, MOCK-HIDE yes). Rejection-gate: Integration is disqualified by behavior phrase \"correct positions in the diff view on the pull request,\" which requires real platform mapping/validation.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed path/line/side (or position) coordinates, then fetch created review comments via API and verify they resolve to intended diff lines in that PR revision.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"PROOF-BUNDLE: (1) Forcing phrase: \"agent identifies at least one real defect\" in a PR with a known bug. (2) Adjacent-lower miss (Integration): a stubbed/model-mocked analyzer can always return a canned defect and pass, so it cannot detect failure of real model judgment on the bug. Generic wiring concerns are not the issue here; the core risk is model decision quality (LLM-DEP yes). Rejection-gate: Workflow disqualified because behavior requires one model-quality outcome, not multiple agentic decisions chained.","test_description":"Run the analyzer with a real model on a benchmark PR containing a seeded known bug; assert at least one posted/generated finding correctly targets that bug class/location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module state consistency: inline-post results (IDs) must be consumed by summary builder for the same run context (MOCK-MISS yes). Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network needed with deterministic API-response fixtures; (b) no AI output quality dependence; (c) no multi-agentic chain; (d) no LLM-governed orchestration requirement. Rejection-gate: System disqualified because requirement is ID correlation logic, testable with in-process wiring.","test_description":"Execute run-state pipeline with mocked comment-post responses containing generated IDs; assert summary payload contains only IDs returned in that run and each summary finding maps to one posted inline comment.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Risk is in module handoff/aggregation between finding collection and summary serialization (MOCK-MISS yes). Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network needed; (b) no dependence on real AI output quality if findings are fixed fixtures; (c) no multi-agentic chain; (d) no LLM decision needed for handoff correctness. Rejection-gate: System disqualified because the failure can be reproduced before HTTP post, at local pipeline boundaries.","test_description":"Feed a multi-finding set through formatter, deduper, and summary payload builder; assert cardinality/content preservation (minus explicit deterministic filters, if any) before post call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real PR and end-to-end API operations; failures include auth, rate limits, API contract mismatches, and ordering across real HTTP calls (REAL-INFRA yes, MOCK-HIDE yes). Rejection-gate: Integration disqualified by phrase \"for a real pull request\" and real posting sequence.","test_description":"Run the automation against an actual repository PR using a fixed finding fixture (no model generation); verify diff retrieval, inline comment creation, and summary post all succeed and are visible via API.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Requires full agent pipeline with real model-generated analysis plus downstream posting and summarization in sequence; correctness depends on chained steps where agentic output drives subsequent actions (MULTI-STEP yes, LLM-DEP yes, REAL-INFRA yes). Rejection-gate: Agentic alone is disqualified by behavior text requiring end-to-end completion across analyze + inline posting + final summary on a real PR, not just model output quality.","test_description":"Execute unattended end-to-end run on a real test PR using real model calls; assert pipeline finishes, inline comments are posted, summary is posted, and summary references run-produced inline artifacts consistently.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
